==French==
===Etymology===
From Vulgar Latin *''casquunus'', a conflation of [[quisque]] [[unus]] ‘each one’ + *''cata unum'', a variant form showing a derivative of Greek [[κατα]] (This variant form survived into Old French as [[chaün]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ʃakœ̃/}}

===Pronoun===
'''chacun''' ''m''
# [[each]], each one, [[every]], [[everyone]]

